text: Elena Perinelli (born 27 June 1995 in Varese) is an Italian volleyball player. She was a member of the Italy women's national volleyball team. She played at the 2012 Women's Junior European Volleyball Championship, 2013 FIVB U20 Volleyball Women's Championship, 2015 Montreux Volley Masters, 2019 Summer Universiade, 2019 FIVB Volleyball Women's Nations League. On the club level, she played for MC Carnaghi Villa Cortese, LJ Volley, and Chieri '76 Volleyball. == References == Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Italian volleyball players Category:Sportspeople from Lombardy Category:People from Varese
